London-based YouTube channel,The UBunifu SpaceÂ is coming to coming to Mzansi. Ubunifu is channel known to many for doing music video reviews, they give an in-depth review of music from any country. They are coming to the country because a huge number of their Youtube subscribers are from Mzansi. With aims to help build and create links for Africans from and outside the continent, Bryan (Kenya), Monique (Zimbabwe/Cameroon), David (Ghana), Sade (Nigeria) and Ian (Uganda) will spend time meeting with creatives, visiting local historic and cultural landmarks and establishing lasting connections with their locally-based online community. They will be in Mzansi from 27 November till 12 December in Johannesburg they will be connecting with their channel lovers and followers through appearances and events to be announced closer to their arrival. 